  <subsection|Use Logical Identities to Rewrite Operations>

  <block|<tformat|<table|<row|<cell|Equivalence>|<cell|Name>>|<row|<cell|<math|p\<rightarrow\>q\<equiv\><around*|(|\<neg\>p\<vee\>q|)>>>|<cell|implication(只有<math|p<rsup|v>=1,q<rsup|v>=0> 为假)>>|<row|<cell|<math|p\<rightarrow\>q\<equiv\>\<neg\>q\<rightarrowlim\>\<neg\>p>>|<cell|Contrapositive(逆否)>>|<row|<cell|<math|p\<leftrightarrow\>q\<equiv\><around*|(|p\<rightarrow\>q|)>\<wedge\><around*|(|q\<rightarrow\>p|)>>>|<cell|Equivalence>>>>>

  \;

  <section|Substitution>

  <subsection|definition>

  <\definition>
    替代<math|A\<rightarrow\>B>

    Suppose <math|A,B\<in\>Form<around*|(|\<cal*-L\><rsup|p>|)>>. B is a substitution instance of A if and only if B may be obtained from A by <with|font-series|bold|substituting formulas> for <with|font-series|bold|propositional variables in A>, replacing every occurrence of the same variable by an occurrence of the same formula.
  </definition>

  （注意，一次只能替换一个A中的原子公式，不允许替换一组合式公式。

  因为A中的合式公式可能是永真或矛盾式，原本真值被限制，替换后因为真值范围扩大可能导致B不成立）

  <subsection|保真定理>

  <\theorem>
    \;

    Suppose <math|A,B\<in\>Form<around*|(|\<cal*-L\><rsup|p>|)>>. If A is a tautology, and B is a substitution of A, then B is a tautology.
  </theorem>

  <\example>
    \;

    <math|p\<rightarrow\><around*|(|q\<rightarrow\>p|)> is a tautology,so its substitution <around*|(|r\<wedge\>s|)>\<rightarrow\><around*|(|q\<rightarrow\><around*|(|r\<wedge\>s|)>|)> is a tautology.>

    \;
  </example>

  <subsection|替代定理>

  <\theorem>
    Substitution theorem

    Suppose <math|A\<in\>Form<around*|(|\<cal*-L\><rsup|p>|)>>. A contain a subformula C (i.e., C is a segment of A and is itself a well-formed formula). If C \<equiv\> D, then replacing some occurrences (not necessarily all) of the subformula C in A with D to obtain the formula B, then A \<equiv\> B.
  </theorem>

  在逻辑恒等式的推理中，这是一个最重要的基本条件。

  Suppose A=ECF, B=EDF.

  If <math|C\<equiv\>D,then A\<equiv\>B>.

  我们在推理时总是没有察觉地使用它。

  <\example>
    \;

    <math|p\<rightarrow\>q\<equiv\><around*|(|\<neg\>p\<vee\>q|)>>

    then, <math|<around*|(|p\<rightarrow\>q|)>\<wedge\><around*|(|r\<rightarrow\><around*|(|p\<rightarrow\>q|)>|)>\<equiv\><around*|(|\<neg\>q\<rightarrow\>p|)>\<wedge\><around*|(|r\<rightarrow\><around*|(|p\<rightarrow\>q|)>|)>>
  </example>

  \;
